project_name: Increase employee productivity using AI tools (ChatGPT / Claude)
project_category: L1. Using external AI tools for basic internal productivity
notes: It was identified that Claude AI requires significant training to be properly used. The tool is considered really more expensive than ChatGPT. This tool is most useful when it is fully integrated with IDE.

project_name: Increase employee productivity using AI tools (ChatGPT / Claude)
project_category: L1. Using external AI tools for basic internal productivity
notes: Claude AI is very different in its functionality and operation versus ChatGPT, and most useful in the hands of senior software engineers. The tool requires training, adoption, and use only in strategic areas of the project, such as architecture and design, in the implementation of the new functionality. Not always useful. Dealing with complex codebases, trying to identify bugs, or implementing code changes in the spaghetti code. Engineering team is adopting a "Train the Trainer" approach, where the tool is released only to engineers that have passed initial training and understand the pros and cons of Cloud AI. It was also identified that ChatGPT is still useful to answer most genetic programming architecture and design questions as well as trying to find code deficiencies or implementing unit tests. These tools are not mutually exclusive.

project_name: Increase employee productivity using AI tools (ChatGPT / Claude)
project_category: L1. Using external AI tools for basic internal productivity
notes: ChatGPT has been released to all engineers within the engineering organization. Claude.ai has been released to two engineers that have passed the training. The engineering team is adopting a "train-the-trainer" approach, where new engineers will be trained before getting accounts on Cloude.ai.
